Sundaram, and Surekha draw on a diverse range of sources, from ethnographic photographs made at the height of the British occupation to hand-painted studio portraits and stills from Bollywood movies. Weighing the influence of the global against the draw of the local, these artists embrace tradition and innovation as covalent rather than competitive forces. Marking the US debut of several of the featured artists, Postdate: Photography and Inherited History in India deepens our understanding of the legacy of colonialism and celebrates new and socially engaged modes of image-making in South Asia.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhotographyzIndiaxHistoryvExhibitions. 4aArt. 4aCollections, Catalogs, Exhibitions. 4aGroup Shows. 7aART / Collections, Catalogs, Exhibitions / Group Shows.2bisacsh1 aCollective, Raqs Media, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGupta, Atreyee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGupta, Atreyee, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGupta, Latika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrane, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThrockmorton, Jodi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThrockmorton, Jodi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028569940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035594140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520355941423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520355941/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deG